author: Chao Deng
title: Asian Markets Wobbly Ahead of
text:
Markets in Asia were off to a weak start, with worries about China’s slowing economic growth in the third quarter, due later Monday, outweighing hopes for stimulus.
Japan’s Nikkei Stock Average was down 0.2%, Australia’s S&P ASX 200 was up 0.3% and South Korea’s Kospi was flat.
